The Institute of Chartered Mediators and Conciliators of Nigeria (ICMC), Ekiti branch,  has called for collaboration between it and Ekiti State Ministry of Justice. Mr. Demola Akinyoade, Chairman of ICMC, Ekiti branch, made the call on Thursday in Ado Ekiti during a courtesy visit to the Attorney General and Commissioner for Justice in the state, Mr Olawale Fapounda. Akinyoade commended the commissioner for his contributions toward the upgrade of the ministry and welfare of members of staff since assuming office in 2018. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! In his remarks, Fapounda said that the ministry was ready to collaborate with the institute in the area of capacity development for members of staff. The commissioner said the ministry would soon commence the implementation of the Multi-Door Courthouse as enshrined in the state administration of Civil Justice Law.